Syntax: anti magic shell

Triggers the Anti Magic Shell finisher skill, surrounding yourself with a
field that disrupts incoming magical attacks. This is a finisher-tier combat
skill: it can only be activated when your combo counter has reached the
required threshold during active combat.

Effects when activated:
  - Grants a +1 hitroll bonus for (combo_count - 3) combat rounds.
  - The combo counter is reset after activation.
  - Skill proficiency improves on successful use.

This is a defensive finisher that improves your attack accuracy rather than
directly reducing damage taken. It is distinct from the Anti Magic Shell
passive/spell effect that grants magical absorption.

Requirements:
  - Must be in combat.
  - Requires a valid finisher combo count.
  - Must have the skill learned.

See also: shelp anti magic shell bash dirt trip
